{
  "text": "Let e 1 (t) be a unit of E 1 . By Lemma 4.5, there is a unit e 2 of E 2 , e 2 \u223c \u03a6(e 1 ) (in the sense of Definition 4.6). By Theorem 8.2 of [CITATION_1] , there are L x, y x, e i (t) e i (t), y for x, y \u2208 D i (t), t > 0.",
