  "bib_entries": {
    "119631785": {
      "title": "Path spaces, continuous tensor products, and E 0 -semigroups",
      "abstract": "We classify all continuous tensor product systems of Hilbert spaces which are \u201cinfinitely divisible\u201d in the sense that they have an associated logarithmic structure. These results are applied to the theory of E 0-semigroups to deduce that every E 0-semigroup possessing sufficiently many \u201cdecomposable\u201d operators must be cocycle conjugate to a CCR flow (Theorem 12.3)."
